Siemens CEO Is ‘Very Bullish’ on U.S., Washington Post Reports

-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 
2011-04-17T14:14:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/siemens-ceo-is-very-bullish-on-u-s-washington-post-reports.html
     April 17 (Bloomberg) -- Siemens AG (SIE)  is “very bullish” on
the U.S. even with the current economic environment, Chief
Executive  Peter Loescher  said in an interview with the
 Washington Post .  The U.S. will continue to upgrade its infrastructure with
rail and energy efficiency projects, he told the newspaper. The
CEO also expects there to be consolidation in the wind-power
industry, Loescher said in the interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 